title: Modular Abandoned Warehouse
description: Modular abandoned warehouse environment for UE4.7 and UE5, featuring static meshes and blueprint assets for lighting and mesh placement.
longDescription:
VIDEO


V2.0 Update: BP_Warehouse provides quick generation of warehouse shell and structure, including doors, walls, windows, structure, and roof modules.


Modular abandoned warehouse environment for UE5, featuring a wide selection of static meshes and blueprint assets for lighting and mesh placement, including 4 demo interior maps. Materials utilize the material layer system for ease of material mixing and inherited parameters.


Architectural elements use fully tile-able seamless layered textures, meaning custom texture maps can be substituted on the base maps while still using layer effects such as water leaks, cracks, dirt, etc. All static mesh foliage types(with the exception of the two plant assets) draw from UV packed textures in a single base material to optimize memory overhead.
technicalDetails:
Features:

  • 114 Static Meshes, including stairways, walls, windows, doors
  • 8 Blueprint Actors
  • Parametric warehouse shell blueprint
  • Chain link fence arrays
  • Basic double door bluprint
  • Mesh linear array with an XYZ axis switch
  • Mesh planar array with vector handle for sizing
  • Hanging light with customizable length
  • Shipping container with operable doors
  • Truss blueprint with adjustable length, height, and structural member thickness
  • 4 demo maps and 1 overview map
  • 4 Materials
  • 58 Material Instances
  • 8 Material Layers
  • 3 Material Layer Blends
  • 2 Material Functions(Optional Procedural Edge Wear & Vertical Paint Blend)
  • Utilizes Unreal Engine's Material Layer system for maximum flexibility
  • 88 Textures, channel packed
  • Decals for graffiti, water stains, and puddles
  • Seamless texture maps for large architecture props for ease of material editing, customization, and swapping out of custom textures


Number of Unique Meshes: 114

Collision: Custom, Nanite, and Generated

Vertex Count: Max 32,045(Tree), Min 4

LODs: Automatic/Nanite

Number of Materials and Material Instances: 4 Materials, 58 Material Instances

Number of Textures: 88

Texture Resolutions: 1K-4K

Supported Development Platforms:

Windows: Yes

Mac: No
